Citation.sTitle: Isobaric Vapor-Liquid Equilibria of the Ternary System Toluene + Ethylbenzene + Amyl Acetate
Citation.sAbstract: Isobaric vapor-liquid equilibria (VLE) was measured for the ternary system toluene + ethylbenzene + amyl acetate. Boiling temperature (T) - liquid composition (x) relations were obtained at (26.66, 53.33, and 79.99) kPa by using a semimicroebulliometer. The Wilson model was used to correlate the binary T-x data and to predict VLE in the ternary system.
